# Quick Start Guide

This guide will help you onboard onto **{{PROJECT_NAME}}** and execute your first development cycle.

---

## 1. Installation & Environment

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```bash
   git clone <repository_url> && cd {{PROJECT_NAME}}
   ```
2. **Setup virtual environment:**
   ```bash
   uv sync
   ```
3. **Install the project CLI or dependencies:**
   Ensure all local packages are built and exposed on your path.

---

## 2. Setting Up Solomon Harness

Initialize the harness in this project by running:

```bash
solomon-harness init
```

This will run a diagnostic check, link the GitHub Project board, scaffold required folders, and index the codebase into your memory store.

---

## 3. Running Workflows

Drive development using the `/solomon-*` commands in your host agent (Claude Code or Gemini CLI):

* Run **`/solomon-loop`** to scan project memory and automatically run the next logical step.
* Run **`/solomon-issue <summary>`** to create a new ticket in the Backlog.
* Run **`/solomon-start <issue_id>`** to begin implementing an issue using TDD.
* Run **`/solomon-release <issue_id>`** to merge and release.
